{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "8f3a2c1e-4b5d-4e8a-9f2c-1234567890ab",
		"name": "SEP API",
		"description": "Colecao Postman da SEP API (Java 21 + Spring Boot 3.5).\n\n**Endpoints cobertos:**\n- Auth Sprint 5 (login, refresh token rotativo, logout, logout-all, /me)\n- MFA TOTP (setup, confirm, verify, disable)\n- Step-up authentication\n- Usuarios (cadastro publico CLIENTE, cadastro interno ADMIN, consulta, listagem, alteracao de senha)\n- Webhooks (Pix/Celcoin com HMAC-SHA256 + Idempotency-Key)\n- Actuator\n- OpenAPI / Swagger\n\n**Variaveis de ambiente esperadas** (collection variables abaixo, sobrescreviveis em environment):\n- baseUrl — http://localhost:8080\n- adminToken / clienteToken — JWTs de acesso\n- adminRefreshToken / clienteRefreshToken — refresh tokens retornados no body no contrato atual\n- adminId / clienteId — UUIDs dos usuarios\n- mfaChallengeId — challenge retornado por /auth/login quando MFA esta ativo\n- stepUpChallengeId / stepUpToken — dados do fluxo step-up\n- webhookSecret — secret HMAC do provider\n\n**Ordem sugerida de execucao local:**\n1. POST /usuarios (criar cliente publico)\n2. Obter/criar admin via seed ou POST /admin/usuarios usando adminToken existente\n3. POST /auth/login (admin/cliente)\n4. Fluxos de MFA/step-up conforme necessidade\n5. Demais requests autenticados\n\n**Nota Sprint 5:** a politica de senha agora e 12+ caracteres OU passphrase; cadastro publico cria sempre CLIENTE. Criacao de ADMIN fica em endpoint autenticado.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Auth",
			"description": "Autenticacao Sprint 5: access token curto, refresh token rotativo, logout e usuario autenticado.",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "POST /auth/login (admin)",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
									"const json = pm.response.json();",
									"if (json.mfaRequired && json.mfaChallengeId) { pm.collectionVariables.set('mfaChallengeId', json.mfaChallengeId); }",
									"if (json.accessToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('adminToken', json.accessToken);",
									"if (json.refreshToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('adminRefreshToken', json.refreshToken);",
									"if (json.usuario?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('adminId', json.usuario.id);"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"v1",
								"auth",
								"login"
							]
						},
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"admin@empresa.com\",\n  \"password\": \"senha-passphrase-segura\"\n}"
						},
						"description": "Login do admin. Se MFA nao estiver ativo, salva adminToken/adminRefreshToken/adminId. Se MFA estiver ativo, salva mfaChallengeId."
					}
				},
